<header>
<div class="container">
<h1>Solid Geometry Calculator (All Shapes)</h1>
</div>
</header>
<main class="container">
<section class="calculator-layout">
<div aria-labelledby="calculator-heading" class="calculator-container">
<h2 id="calculator-heading">Interactive Solid Geometry Calculator</h2>
<form id="geometry-form">
<div class="form-group">
<label for="shape">Select Shape *</label>
<select aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="shape">
<option value="sphere">Sphere</option>
<option value="cube">Cube</option>
<option value="cylinder">Cylinder</option>
<!-- Additional shapes can be added here -->
</select>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="dimension">Enter Dimension *</label>
<input aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="dimension" placeholder="e.g., 5" type="number"/>
</div>
<button class="btn-primary" onclick="calculate()" type="button">Calculate</button>
</form>
<div aria-live="polite" class="error-message" id="error-message" role="alert"></div>
</div>
<div class="results-container" id="results">
<h3>Results</h3>
<div id="volume-result">Volume: <span id="volume-value">0</span></div>
<div id="surface-area-result">Surface Area: <span id="surface-area-value">0</span></div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="content-container">
<h2>Data Source and Methodology</h2>
<p>All calculations are based on standard geometric formulas. <a href="https://www.calculatorsoup.com/calculators/geometry-solids/index.php">Source</a>.</p>
<h2>The Formula Explained</h2>
<div class="formula-box">
<p><strong>Sphere Volume:</strong> \( V = \frac{4}{3} \pi r^3 \)</p>
<p><strong>Sphere Surface Area:</strong> \( SA = 4 \pi r^2 \)</p>
</div>
<h2>Glossary of Terms</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Volume:</strong> The amount of space occupied by the shape.</li>
<li><strong>Surface Area:</strong> The total area of the surface of a three-dimensional object.</li>
</ul>
<h2>How It Works: A Step-by-Step Example</h2>
<p>To calculate the volume of a sphere with a radius of 5:</p>
<p>\( V = \frac{4}{3} \pi (5^3) = 523.6 \) cubic units.</p>
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3>What is a solid geometry calculator?</h3>
<p>A solid geometry calculator helps you calculate the volume and surface area of various solid shapes.</p>
<h3>How accurate are the calculations?</h3>
<p>The calculations are based on standard mathematical formulas and are accurate to the precision of the input data.</p>
<h3>Can I use this calculator for educational purposes?</h3>
<p>Yes, this calculator is perfect for students and educators alike.</p>
</section>
<section class="author-box">
<p>Tool developed by <strong>Ugo Candido</strong>. Content reviewed by the CalcDomain Expert Team. Last reviewed for accuracy on: October 20, 2023.</p>
</section>
</main>

<script defer="">
        function calculate() {
            const shape = document.getElementById('shape').value;
            const dimension = parseFloat(document.getElementById('dimension').value);
            let volume = 0;
            let surfaceArea = 0;
            let errorMessage = '';

            if (isNaN(dimension) || dimension <= 0) {
                errorMessage = 'Please enter a valid dimension greater than zero.';
                document.getElementById('error-message').textContent = errorMessage;
                return;
            }

            switch (shape) {
                case 'sphere':
                    volume = (4 / 3) * Math.PI * Math.pow(dimension, 3);
                    surfaceArea = 4 * Math.PI * Math.pow(dimension, 2);
                    break;
                case 'cube':
                    volume = Math.pow(dimension, 3);
                    surfaceArea = 6 * Math.pow(dimension, 2);
                    break;
                case 'cylinder':
                    volume = Math.PI * Math.pow(dimension, 2) * dimension;
                    surfaceArea = 2 * Math.PI * dimension * (dimension + dimension);
                    break;
                default:
                    errorMessage = 'Invalid shape selected.';
                    break;
            }

            if (!errorMessage) {
                document.getElementById('volume-value').textContent = volume.toFixed(2);
                document.getElementById('surface-area-value').textContent = surfaceArea.toFixed(2);
                document.getElementById('error-message').textContent = '';
            } else {
                document.getElementById('error-message').textContent = errorMessage;
            }
        }
    </script>


